1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,336
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:06,172
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,719
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,802 --> 00:00:12,887
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:17,767
♪ <i>In the tangle…</i> ♪

7
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:19,436
[Janine] <i>You were just given away</i>
<i>when you were a baby.</i>

8
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:22,188
Maybe you were snotty,
so they didn't love you!

9
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:25,734
Ibyang, nothing! No parents!

10
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:27,277
Ibyang, nothing!

11
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,446
No parents!

12
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:32,532
Ibyang, nothing! No parents!

13
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:33,867
What is that for?

14
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:35,785
[Atoy] <i>So, I can talk to Sister Norma.</i>

15
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:39,164
<i>They said she's the only one who knows</i>
<i>where Ibyang really came from.</i>

16
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:40,749
[Cita] <i>Be careful.</i>

17
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:44,377
<i>You never know, a snake might slither in.</i>

18
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,628
[Martina, in English]
<i>We can talk to her tomorrow.</i>

19
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:47,922
[in English] She does not know my name,
but I am sure she will remember my face.

20
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:49,883
- Come with me.
- [in English] Yes, Boss.

21
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:51,342
Do you still have food?

22
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:54,345
[Atoy, woman's voice] Hmm, Sister,
maybe you have something kept aside?

23
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:56,431
[Sister Ludy] <i>They said</i>
<i>she left a child with you.</i>

24
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:57,849
<i>Do you remember?</i>

25
00:00:57,932 --> 00:01:00,602
<i>Are they the parents of the child</i>
<i>they are looking for?</i>

26
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:02,145
[nun 1] <i>Who are they?</i>

27
00:01:02,228 --> 00:01:03,563
[nun 2] <i>They said a married couple.</i>

28
00:01:03,646 --> 00:01:06,274
<i>But I did not get their names.</i>

29
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:08,777
[nun 3] <i>But why would they look for her</i>
<i>if they already gave the child away?</i>

30
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:12,655
Ah, Sister, Sister Norma's quarters
are still being prepared.

31
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:15,158
[nun] <i>Just bring that to the Rose Garden.</i>

32
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:16,576
<i>She is there.</i>

33
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:17,952
[Sister Ludy] Sister…

34
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:21,372
Why are you the one bringing food
to Sister Norma?

35
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:22,791
PREVIOUSLY

36
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:23,792
[music swells]

37
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:25,251
Sister?

38
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,545
[music fades]

39
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:29,964
[in English] Sister, can I see you?

40
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:32,801
Sister.

41
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:36,262
[rousing music playing]

42
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:46,022
- [clangs]
- [squeals]

43
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:47,941
[Sister Ludy] My God! Oh my God! My God…

44
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:50,777
[in English] Sister.
Sister, I'm so sorry. Sister.

45
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:53,321
Quick, let's help. Sister, be careful.

46
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:54,697
[in English] I'm so sorry, Sister.

47
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:56,282
Help her clean.

48
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,867
- [nun 1] Ah, let's go.
- [Sister Ludy] Ask for help.

49
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,869
[Sister Ludy] Be careful.

50
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:02,705
[upbeat music playing]

51
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:13,550
Back to work.

52
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:15,885
Back to work. Go on. Leave her be.

53
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,013
[suave theme music playing]

54
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,932
[motorcycle revving]

55
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:21,891
[sewing machine whirring]

56
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,810
[scratches]

57
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:24,853
[snipping]

58
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,354
[whirring]

59
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:28,731
[sewing machine whirring]

60
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,942
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots blasting]

61
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,777
[gunshots blasting]

62
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:35,822
[snipping]

63
00:02:40,034 --> 00:02:41,661
[electronic blipping]

64
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:44,622
[music fades]

65
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:47,333
Ma'am, you need to eat,

66
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:48,793
so you can regain your strength

67
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:50,795
and you can find your child.

68
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:53,464
Ma'am, even if you have not seen her,

69
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:55,884
she is also looking for you.

70
00:02:55,967 --> 00:03:00,555
The bond between mother
and child cannot be broken.

71
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:10,273
[somber music playing]

72
00:03:10,356 --> 00:03:14,360
Ma'am, maybe this can help in your search.

73
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:17,947
St. Anthony de Padua, patron of the lost.

74
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:27,290
[melancholic music playing]

75
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:32,754
[sighs]

76
00:03:42,388 --> 00:03:44,515
[Ibyang] <i>Thread in the needle.</i>

77
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:47,352
It passes but does not stop.

78
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,481
It passes but does not stop.

79
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:58,279
[melancholic music playing]

80
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:34,524
[music fades]

81
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,734
IBYANG, NOTHING!
NO PARENTS!

82
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,569
[unsettling music playing]

83
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,989
I do not want to be
in this school anymore.

84
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,075
People here are mean.

85
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:50,081
[music continues]

86
00:04:56,587 --> 00:04:59,048
[music fades]

87
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:02,802
[muffled chattering in the distance]

88
00:05:04,762 --> 00:05:07,432
[sneaky music playing]

89
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:24,615
- [music fades]
- [muffled chattering in the distance]

90
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:31,164
[phone vibrating]

91
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,375
[phone blips]

92
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:36,753
Uh, excuse me.

93
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:41,507
Do you know where the former property
of Tahanan ng Bukas is?

94
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:45,053
The former orphanage that burned down.

95
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:46,679
That's it.

96
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:49,766
This is the former property
of the orphanage.

97
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:52,226
The building itself was demolished.

98
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:56,230
A condo is being built,
so it is fenced off.

99
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:59,317
[somber music playing]

100
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,359
Are you okay, ma'am?

101
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:01,986
[sentimental music playing]

102
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:06,240
My child was left at Tahanan ng Bukas.

103
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:09,994
The orphanage is gone.

104
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,289
All right, thank you.

105
00:06:22,298 --> 00:06:23,466
My God.

106
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:28,262
Please do not erase me yet
from my child's life.

107
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,850
Wherever she is…

108
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:40,817
I hope you still give me
a chance to be with her.

109
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,372
[music fades]

110
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:59,043
[suspicious music playing]

111
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:33,661
- [music fades]
- [muffled chattering in the distance]

112
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:44,046
No, no, no, no, no! Do not sit there.

113
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:47,383
Do not sit there, miss.
Um, the paint is not dry yet.

114
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:50,511
I sat there earlier.

115
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:53,181
- My skirt got a little stained.
- Oh, no!

116
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,893
Um, sit here instead.

117
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,811
[bright music playing]

118
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,188
Nothing?

119
00:08:00,813 --> 00:08:04,025
You should have told me first that
the nun I grabbed was the wrong one.

120
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,234
Then I would not have embarrassed myself.

121
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:06,527
Why?

122
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:09,614
Would it change what you did
if she was indeed Sister Norma?

123
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:10,781
First of all, hon,

124
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,408
you should not be causing trouble.

125
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,410
[in English] How on earth
are we gonna come back here now?

126
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,536
We've made a bad impression.

127
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:18,539
That vow of silence is nonsense.

128
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:22,001
Look, if I point a gun at her,
she will do a monologue.

129
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:23,961
Why didn't we just do that?

130
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,671
[suspicious music playing]

131
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:28,424
Oh… [in English] Can you
just please shut up?

132
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:30,718
[in English] He has a point.

133
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:35,097
You know, we cannot persuade those nuns.
They need to be threatened.

134
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:39,644
Tonight. Let's come back here, break in,

135
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:41,854
corner Sister Norma.

136
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,857
My God. Hon, is that really necessary?

137
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:46,901
You said it yourself, didn't you?

138
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:49,153
We've made a bad impression,
so I will go all the way.

139
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:51,948
Right, Boss. I saw
the side entrance gate earlier,

140
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,533
where the nuns passed.

141
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:55,034
It looks easier to slip through there.

142
00:08:56,577 --> 00:08:57,453
[in English] Fine.

143
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,580
Just don't get caught. Okay?

144
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:02,333
[music fades]

145
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:05,169
[Ibyang sighs]

146
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:10,174
[chattering in the distance]

147
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,885
- There.
- Ibyang… nothing?

148
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,555
Is your name Ibyang?

149
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:17,640
What?

150
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,772
Are you being bullied at school?

151
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:30,111
[melancholic music playing]

152
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:36,284
I'm not doing anything to them.

153
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,412
I don't want to think of them.

154
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:42,582
I will just cut them from my mind.

155
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,086
Then why…

156
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:51,257
do you still look sad?

157
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:56,387
Let me see your smile.

158
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:58,848
Smile. Let me see your smile.

159
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,101
Hmm, smile, hmm, hmm, hmm.

160
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:04,562
Your smile is beautiful! [gasps]

161
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:07,690
This is the first time
I've seen such a beautiful smile.

162
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:10,735
Hmm, hmm.

163
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:12,236
[light music playing]

164
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:15,156
You know, Ibyang,

165
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:18,534
you look even more beautiful
when you smile.

166
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:21,203
So, always smile.

167
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:28,961
What they said,
that you are nothing, is not true.

168
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,129
You have worth.

169
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:34,258
Especially to the people you help.
Like me!

170
00:10:34,342 --> 00:10:37,803
Earlier, you kept me
from getting my clothes dirty, right?

171
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:41,557
And especially to the people who love you,

172
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,601
like your parents.

173
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,896
[sentimental music playing]

174
00:10:47,688 --> 00:10:49,106
Ibyang.

175
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:52,276
Don't cry anymore.

176
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:58,032
Cry it all out to me.

177
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,952
Let out all your anger.

178
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:08,334
Go ahead, child.

179
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,337
[in English] It's okay.

180
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:15,508
[in English] It's okay, baby girl.

181
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,476
Don't cry anymore.

182
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,727
[chuckles softly]

183
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:29,855
[Audrey sniffles]

184
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:31,524
That's enough.

185
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:36,779
[music fades]

186
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,509
[sneaky music playing]

187
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,226
Sister Norma.

188
00:12:14,358 --> 00:12:15,901
Do not be afraid of me.

189
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:19,488
I am Atoy. I just… I just
need to know something from you.

190
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,200
I know you have a vow of silence.

191
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:28,414
Sister Norma, I just need to know
something from you.

192
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,084
Ah, don't… don't worry.

193
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:34,003
I have no ill intent.

194
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:36,797
[ominous music playing]

195
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:39,884
I have something important…
Sister? Wait, Sister.

196
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:42,303
Hold on, hold on.

197
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:46,182
[foreboding music playing]

198
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:10,372
[grunts]

199
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:14,168
[suspicious music playing]

200
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:22,885
[Atoy] I'm sorry.

201
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:25,804
You almost had an accident because of me.

202
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:29,808
Thank you.

203
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,227
[music swells]

204
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,191
[music fades]

205
00:13:37,274 --> 00:13:38,943
[sobs]

206
00:13:40,027 --> 00:13:42,238
Why are you crying too?

207
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,781
[Audrey sniffs]

208
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:45,991
Were you also bullied at…

209
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:53,457
Something like that…
They conspired against me.

210
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,043
[somber music playing]

211
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:59,505
[in English] But this isn't about me.

212
00:14:00,756 --> 00:14:01,924
Ibyang…

213
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,886
Don't let what they say
affect you too much.

214
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,889
Most of the time,

215
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:13,644
bullies have problems at home
or in their own families.

216
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:20,150
That's why they release their anger
at school or on other people.

217
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,237
They carry their negativity.

218
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,866
What if…

219
00:14:28,158 --> 00:14:30,119
they don't stop?

220
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:36,041
Then report them
to the teacher or fight back!

221
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,334
Let me see your muscles.

222
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:39,545
Show me.

223
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:42,006
Oh! Wow!

224
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:43,382
They're big.

225
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:47,761
Confront them. Tell them,
"That's bad! Stop it!"

226
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:49,096
Like that!

227
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:51,432
[bright music playing]

228
00:14:52,683 --> 00:14:55,686
How old are you, Ibyang?

229
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,939
Eight years old.

230
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,065
Eight?

231
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:03,319
You're the same age as my child.

232
00:15:05,487 --> 00:15:09,116
- [Audrey chuckles]
- She's lucky to have you as her mom.

233
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,744
[chuckles softly]

234
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:14,997
[sentimental music playing]

235
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:17,041
[chuckles]

236
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:18,709
You're really cute.

237
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:31,555
What's your snack today?

238
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:37,811
[Ibyang] Just take my snack.
As a thank you.

239
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:41,023
This looks delicious! [sniffs]

240
00:15:42,566 --> 00:15:45,736
But I can't eat this.

241
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:48,155
I'm only to eat soft food now,

242
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:51,742
food that's easy to chew,

243
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:53,786
because I just had surgery.

244
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,080
Ah.

245
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,375
[Ibyang] Ah.

246
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:04,129
If you're here tomorrow morning,

247
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:07,675
I'll bring you soft food.

248
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:09,843
- [Audrey] Oh, wow!
- What would you like?

249
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:13,013
Mmm-hmm. Anything!

250
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:16,350
Uh, what about you?

251
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:18,560
Do you like cookies?

252
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,938
Because cookies are my favorite.

253
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:22,940
But I'm not allowed to eat them yet,

254
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:25,609
so I'll just bake some for you.

255
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:26,735
If you want.

256
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,571
- I'd love that!
- Wow!

257
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,365
- I'll bring you some tomorrow?
- Yes.

258
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:33,409
Let's exchange snacks tomorrow.

259
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:34,868
That's great.

260
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,829
Uh, don't you have a class?

261
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:37,997
[music stops]

262
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,749
- Uh… Uh, no.
- [bright music playing]

263
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,627
Um, it's the principal's
birthday tomorrow,

264
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:45,587
so we have a free day.

265
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:47,339
[in English] Perfect.

266
00:16:47,423 --> 00:16:49,633
[sniffles]

267
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:51,051
See you?

268
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,846
See you.

269
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:56,015
- We'll see each other tomorrow.
- Okay.

270
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:57,933
- Promise that.
- Promise.

271
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,146
Oh, you're beautiful!

272
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:04,273
I told you so.

273
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:11,864
I'm sorry. I pretended to be a nun.

274
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,951
This was the only way I could talk to you.

275
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:24,585
Sister.

276
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:32,551
[in English] Ivy Santos, eight years old.

277
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:34,678
[melancholic music playing]

278
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:36,805
We call her Ibyang.

279
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:40,476
She's a good child, but…

280
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,771
a little mischievous
and sassy, but still kind.

281
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:46,857
I'm already sending her to school.

282
00:17:49,818 --> 00:17:51,487
Sister,

283
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:57,618
you are listed as the finder
on her foundling certificate.

284
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:03,791
Sister, do you remember her?

285
00:18:05,209 --> 00:18:06,960
She is eight years old now.

286
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,672
Do you recognize her?

287
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:18,305
Where did you… find her?
Did her parents give her to you?

288
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,184
[music fades]

289
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:24,144
[Norma] Such a cute baby.

290
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,772
Where are her parents?

291
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:31,693
Uh… Her mother is in a coma and, um,

292
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:33,987
she might not wake up.

293
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:38,367
So, I'm entrusting the child to you.

294
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:40,077
[titters]

295
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:43,330
But what if the mother wakes up

296
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,707
and looks for her child?

297
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,293
What are the parents' names?

298
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:49,336
[in English] I'm sorry, Sister.

299
00:18:49,419 --> 00:18:52,172
But I-I don't think you…
you have to know that… Um…

300
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:55,300
You take care of her.

301
00:18:55,384 --> 00:18:58,345
[in English] I'm sure you can find
a suitable home for her.

302
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,430
[somber music playing]

303
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:02,015
What is the baby's name?

304
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:03,934
[Martina] Uh…

305
00:19:05,185 --> 00:19:07,312
She isn't registered yet.

306
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:11,150
I was hoping
you could also take care of that.

307
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:17,322
Um…

308
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:22,452
I don't accept money, miss.

309
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:27,583
No, Sister, please accept it,
just for all the trouble.

310
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:30,419
[in English] I have to go. I'm sorry.

311
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:32,754
Wait, miss. Miss, wait!

312
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:35,299
Miss, what is your name?

313
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:39,970
[pensive music playing]

314
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:46,101
Eight years ago, my wife
gave you a two-month-old baby.

315
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:48,562
Her name is Martina. Ma-Martina Regalia.

316
00:19:48,645 --> 00:19:49,938
Do you remember?

317
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:51,773
Sister, do you still remember me?

318
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:53,400
We just want to find the child.

319
00:19:53,483 --> 00:19:55,569
We want to know who adopted her.

320
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:57,070
[sinister music playing]

321
00:19:57,154 --> 00:20:02,034
Sister, I just want Ibyang
to know her parents.

322
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:09,750
We will accept it if they
abandon her or ignore her.

323
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:12,544
What matters is knowing, as she grows up,

324
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:15,047
who her real parents are.

325
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:16,840
[suspicious music playing]

326
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:18,717
If that happens,

327
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,928
I will not neglect her.

328
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:26,850
Sister, I'm sorry.

329
00:20:26,934 --> 00:20:30,354
I know you have a vow of silence,
and I respect that.

330
00:20:30,437 --> 00:20:34,816
But maybe there is a way for you
to tell me

331
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,236
where I can find her parents.

332
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:46,203
Sister, maybe you can just write it down.

333
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:50,791
Please.

334
00:21:08,809 --> 00:21:10,686
[nun 1] Sister Norma?

335
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:15,774
[tense music playing]

336
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:27,911
Sister, your things have been moved
to St. Therese House.

337
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:32,082
Your food will be brought there
so you can rest.

338
00:21:35,210 --> 00:21:36,837
[music swells]

339
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:44,803
[suspicious music playing]

340
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:56,440
8 P.M. BELL TOWER
LET'S TALK

341
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:27,304
[in English] 1500 hours.

342
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:28,930
There's still time.

343
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:41,193
[music fades]

344
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:43,695
[tense music playing]

345
00:23:04,508 --> 00:23:07,969
That's where the nuns passed
after handing out food earlier.

346
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:11,139
That's fine. There's only one guard.

347
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,643
But there's CCTV.

348
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:17,687
[gun cocks]

349
00:23:20,482 --> 00:23:23,026
[music fades]

350
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:27,572
[ominous music playing]

351
00:23:27,656 --> 00:23:28,990
[gunshot, glass breaks]

352
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:31,535
[music continues]

353
00:23:31,618 --> 00:23:32,869
[gunshot, glass breaks]

354
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:40,710
[music swells]

355
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:46,383
- [grunts]
- Where is Sister Norma?

356
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:47,843
- I don't know, sir!
- Hmm?

357
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:49,302
I really don't know, sir!

358
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:50,887
- [grunts]
- [bone cracks]

359
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:55,684
[foreboding music playing]

360
00:24:06,236 --> 00:24:07,737
[sighs]

361
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:10,824
- Take care of that.
- [in English] Yes, Boss.

362
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:13,910
[grunting]

363
00:24:13,994 --> 00:24:15,871
[man sighs]

364
00:24:28,508 --> 00:24:32,470
[electronic blipping]

365
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:36,016
[tense music playing]

366
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:40,145
[Mongki] Whoever you are, come out!

367
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:42,939
[grunting and groaning]

368
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:44,816
UP NEXT

369
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,401
[bone cracks]

370
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:47,819
[grunting and groaning]

371
00:24:48,862 --> 00:24:49,988
Who are you?

372
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:52,032
What do you want with Sister Norma?

373
00:24:52,115 --> 00:24:53,366
[grunts] What are you?

374
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,576
A gay nun, huh?

375
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:56,703
- [pants, then gasps]
- [gunshot]

376
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:58,622
I knew it!

377
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:01,750
- Atoy is looking for Ibyang's parents!
- Ame.

378
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:02,792
[gasps]

379
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:04,085
[in English] Sorry, sorry, sorry.

380
00:25:04,169 --> 00:25:06,379
Master Grumpy is looking for my parents?

381
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:07,881
[music intensifies]

382
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:09,174
- [grunts]
- [bell tolls]

383
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:11,009
[groans]

384
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:13,470
[Red] Let's finish this
if you don't want to get hurt.

385
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,096
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

386
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,057
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

387
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:20,602
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

388
00:25:20,685 --> 00:25:22,354
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

389
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:23,605
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
